RACE.FOOTNOTES: RASTAMAN VIBE tucked inside early giving chase, hugged the rail to the stretch, roused at the top of the lane but got boxed in, found an opening along the inside midstretch and drove past outer rivals. GUY NAMED JOE threw his head and hit the gate, traveled two wide then moved inside racing at the back, drew closer in the middle stages, angled out into the lane, rallied and got up for second. BANDWAGON stalked three deep, pushed on through the far turn still in the three path, challenged midstretch but got outkicked. LET SEAMUS GO forwardly placed three deep on the clubhouse turn, applied pressure from outside on the backstretch, fought outside the lead into the final furlong, took over at the sixteenth pole but was outkicked in the end. POTENTIAL SPAM settled inside then had to steady into the first turn, traveled along the inside, moved off the rail and went two wide into the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and came with a mild late bid. SINE QUA NON was off slow to begin, raced three wide or outside a rival on the first turn, trailed into the second bend, got forced out into the stretch, had the rider lose his whip in the lane, still showed a mild rally to gain late, dismounted on the backstretch following the race and walked into the van. ARIO broke a step slow, got bumped and put in tight early, stalked keenly along the inside into the first turn, tipped two wide leaving the second bend, got boxed in upper stretch and finished willingly. MAXIMUM CAPACITY sped clear from inside, took pressure on the backstretch, maintained a short lead around the far turn and into the stretch, battled into the final furlong, lost command at the sixteenth pole and weakened late. BOLT AT MIDNIGHT off slow in the beginning, saved ground through both turns and kept trying through the lane while unable to threaten. TRACKER tracked in the two path, three deep at the quarter pole, brushed with inner rival at the eight pole and could not rally. NESSO'S LASTHARRAH raced up close between rivals early then dropped back a bit to give chase still between foes, found traffic at the eighth pole and could not rally after. WHEN HEROES FLY raced two wide near the back, traveled outside a rival on the far turn, swung out into the lane, moved back inward in upper stretch and came up empty.

GLORY OF CHROME dropped back early, saved ground through the turn, angled out in upper stretch, moved back in some approaching the sixteenth pole and missed the show. BLACKENED vied between rivals into and around the bend, lost touch with the leaders in upper stretch and weakened. WILLAMINA was off a bit slow to begin, chased two then three wide on the turn and failed to menace. TURQUOISE BIKINI took control early and held a slim lead over outer trio in the early going, battled along the rail through the turn, lost the advantage at the quarter pole and gave way down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAY HOT settled outside a pair of rivals at the back, continued three deep into the far turn, swung widest into the lane, rallied from the middle of the stretch and bested ROTHSCHILD and MIRACLE MARK in deep stretch. ROTHSCHILD unhurried on the inside early, drew closer up the backstretch, had to wait when boxed in through the far turn, roused when gaining an opening entering the lane, launched a bid from the fence, took over midstretch but got outkicked by the winner. MIRACLE MARK rated on the fence early, stalked two wide into the second bend, tipped out entering the stretch, launched a bid outside CHARGE FOR GOLD, fought between rivals in the final sixteenth but was also outkicked. LORD BULLINGDON traveled between rivals at the rear, angled four wide into the stretch, lacked room and had to alter back toward the inside at the top of the lane, summoned a mild rally and earned a minor award. CHARGE FOR GOLD dueled outside INVINCIBLE through both turns, held a short lead three wide into the stretch, lost command midstretch and weakened. DEADPAN sat off the pace outside a rival, chased three wide into the far turn, came under a ride and angled out to leave that bend in the five path but flattened in the stretch run. ALWAYS ON CAY stalked keenly in hand from the two path early, drew alongside the top pair at the half-mile pole, stayed alongside through the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and weakened. INVINCIBLE dueled inside CHARGE FOR GOLD for command, battled two wide into the stretch and gave way in the final furlong. JUST A GUESS tucked inside racing at the back early, trailed into the stretch and had little left for the drive.

SHARPAZANO pressed the pace from inside, headed EXPRESS LINE on the turn, dueled into and down the lane and finished gamely in defeat. BOWTIE BOYS forwardly placed in the early going, rounded the bend three then four wide, finished willingly under right then left handed urging but lacked the needed late punch to get by the top pair. LAST CALL PAUL stalked wide up the backstretch, rounded the bend four to five wide and lacked a bid. Closed with 1 (Queen Goddess) $4,500 additional to start, with $300,000 Guaranteed, of which $180,000 to first, $60,000 to second, $36,000 to third, $18,000 to fourth and $6,000 to fifth. Three-year-olds 120 lbs. Older 123 lbs. Starters to be named through the entry box by closing time of en tries. First preference will be given to Gr I or Gr II winners in 2023. Second preference will be given to horses placed (second or third) in a Gr I or Gr II or Gr III winners in 2023. Total non-claiming earnings in 2023 will be used in determining the or der of preference of horses with equal status. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SURGE CAPACITY came in sharply at the start, settled inside, drew closer in the middle stages, continued to save ground on the far turn, ran into traffic behind GRACELUND GRAY in upper stretch, snuck through along the fence at the eight pole, surged late and edged FLUFFY SOCKS in the closing moments. FLUFFY SOCKS traveled three deep at the back, advanced while angling out to the five path on the far turn, stormed to the front with a sixteenth remaining but got outclosed SURGE CAPACITY late. BEAUTE CACHEE (FR) stalked in the two path then near the inside, coaxed along into the far turn, chased two wide into the lane, bumped with inner rival in upper stretch, angled out in the furlong grounds and rallied for the show. WHITEBEAM (GB) rated in the two path, drew alongside the leader with three furlongs remaining, dueled into the lane, took over in upper stretch, put away inner rival midstretch but was soon overtaken with a sixteenth left to run and flattened to third. RUBY NELL tracked two wide into the first turn then moved out to the four path, was on the move outside rivals around the second bend, raced in the four path turning for home, finished willingly but was outkicked in deep stretch. CLOSING REMARKS unhurried early on and moved into the two path, continued two wide to the stretch, steered to the inside bothering a rival in upper stretch and kept on to improve position. ELM DRIVE stalked four then three wide on the clubhouse turn, took aim and asked three wide entering the stretch but flattened out in the late stages. GRACELUND GRAY stepped to the front and moved inside, pressured from outside into the far turn, dueled into the lane, lost command in upper stretch and weakened. QUEEN GODDESS steadied between rivals on the clubhouse turn, tracked out of range off the rail, rounded the far turn three deep and lacked a response when called upon. HAMWOOD FLIER (IRE) forwardly placed in the early going on the inside, chased a bit off the rail into the drive, bumped with outer rival in upper stretch and weakened. WAKANAKA (IRE) tossed her head leaving the gate and dropped back to last, steered to the inside, came off the rail and trailed four wide into the lane, moved out further in the stretch and was not a factor. ELOUNDA QUEEN (IRE) off slow to begin, traveled along the rail towards the rear, steadied in tight at the eighth pole and never made an impact.

MISS WORLD PEACE chased off the inside, driven five wide into the lane, challenged in upper stretch, outkicked by the winner in the furlong grounds and stayed on to secure second. DREAMING OF HOPE stalked three deep into the turn, challenged from outside around the bend, dueled four wide into the lane and flattened in the late stages. CAPO SORELLA closest in pursuit up the backstretch, challenged from outside into the turn, put away CONQUEST CELSIUS at the quarter pole then fought inside DREAMING OF HOPE late on the bend, lost command in upper stretch and gave way in the final furlong.
